cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of image recognition tasks using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new module for enhancing the spatial grouping of semantic features, which involves attention mechanisms and optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various object detection tasks, which may also make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
